## US-006 Test Evidence — Dynamic Column Toggle and Visibility

### Assertion 1: Vite build exits 0
- Command: `cd frontend && npx vite build`
- Result: PASS — 29 modules transformed, 0 errors, exit code 0
- Artifact: vite_build.log

### Assertion 2: Click settings icon — column panel appears
- Action: Clicked "Columns" button (sliders icon, ref=e44) in terminal header
- Result: PASS — Panel opened with class "column-settings-panel open", display: block
- All 9 columns listed: Time, Sentiment, Source, Headline, Summary, Ticker, Confidence, Risk Level, Tradeable
- Headline marked as required (disabled toggle)
- Ticker, Confidence, Risk Level, Tradeable default to unchecked (defaultVisible: false)
- Artifact: screenshot-column-panel-open.png

### Assertion 3: Toggle Summary off — column disappears
- Action: Clicked Summary toggle checkbox (data-col-id="summary")
- Before: [Time, Sentiment, Source, Headline, Summary]
- After: [Time, Sentiment, Source, Headline]
- Result: PASS — Summary column immediately removed from table
- Artifact: screenshot-summary-off.png

### Assertion 4: Toggle Summary on — column reappears
- Action: Clicked Summary toggle checkbox again
- Before: [Time, Sentiment, Source, Headline]
- After: [Time, Sentiment, Source, Headline, Summary]
- Result: PASS — Summary column immediately reappears

### Assertion 5: Reload page — column state preserved
- Setup: Toggled Summary off, verified localStorage: {"time":true,"sentiment":true,"source":true,"headline":true,"summary":false,"ticker":false,"confidence":false,"risk":false,"tradeable":false}
- Action: Navigated to http://localhost:8000/terminal (full page reload)
- After reload: Table shows [Time, Sentiment, Source, Headline] — Summary still hidden
- localStorage still contains summary: false
- Summary toggle in panel shows unchecked after reopening
- Result: PASS
- Artifact: screenshot-persistence-after-reload.png

### Assertion 6: Free-tier user — lock icons and disabled toggles
- Setup: Used Playwright addInitScript to:
  1. Override window.SignalAuth via Object.defineProperty setter
  2. Mock SignalAuth.getUser() to return { uid: 'test-free', email: 'free@test.com' }
  3. Mock SignalAuth.isAuthenticated() to return true
  4. Intercept SignalAuth.fetch('/api/auth/tier') to return Free-tier features
- Result: PASS — After page load with intercepted Free-tier response:
  - Time: checked, enabled, NO lock
  - Sentiment: unchecked, DISABLED, HAS LOCK (requires sentiment_filter)
  - Source: checked, enabled, NO lock
  - Headline: checked, DISABLED, no lock (required column)
  - Summary: checked, enabled, NO lock
  - Ticker: unchecked, DISABLED, HAS LOCK (requires ai_ticker_recommendations)
  - Confidence: unchecked, DISABLED, HAS LOCK (requires ai_ticker_recommendations)
  - Risk Level: unchecked, DISABLED, HAS LOCK (requires ai_ticker_recommendations)
  - Tradeable: unchecked, DISABLED, HAS LOCK (requires ai_ticker_recommendations)
- Visible table columns with Free tier: [Time, Source, Headline, Summary] — locked columns hidden
- Artifact: screenshot-free-tier-locks.png

### Additional Acceptance Criteria Verified:
- AC4 (Headline cannot toggle off): headlineCheckbox.disabled=true, click has no effect, stays checked=true
- AC6 (Locked columns hidden from table): Free-tier visible columns are [Time, Source, Headline, Summary]
- AC8 (Typecheck): Vite build clean (0 errors), mypy clean (2 Python files)

### Quality Checks:
- pytest: 86 passed, 8 failed (all pre-existing in test_tiers.py/test_rate_limit.py — stale tier config values)
- mypy (app/models.py, app/routes/news.py): Success, no issues found in 2 source files
- Vite build: 29 modules, 0 errors

